{"word":"ἀκηδής","slug":"ἀκηδής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀκηδής</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κῆδος'><el>κῆδος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>uncared for, unburied</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>without care</i> or <i>sorrow, careless, heedless</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}